{
  "texts": [
    "Kobayashi et al. [134] considered a memoryless multiple access channel where the transmitter aims to send the communication information and estimate the channel state simultaneously.",
    "Moreover, they investigated the capacity-distortion tradeoff to bridge information theory and the estimation theory.",
    "Also, Ahmadipour et al. [135] focused on the capacity-distortion tradeoff under memoryless transmission channels.",
    "Moreover, Joudeh et al. [136] investigated the tradeoff between reliable message communication and state detection, verifying the superiority of ISAC.In addition, the performance tradeoff between two functionalities within different ISAC systems has been investigated.",
    "For example, considering the correlated sensing and channel state, Liu et al. [137] investigated the performance trade-off of ISAC for vehicular systems, which was evaluated by a capacity distortion function."
  ]
}